18:19.190 --> 18:20.242
Ms. Barry?

18:21.661 --> 18:22.458
Yes?

18:23.413 --> 18:25.664
Hi. It's Frankie Heck.
(stammers)

18:26.070 --> 18:27.277
May I help you?

18:27.367 --> 18:32.405
Uh, well, I-I just
wanted to explain, um,

18:32.440 --> 18:35.385
why my husband Mike
never called you back.

18:35.726 --> 18:37.745
I mean, I'm sure you have been
wondering about it

18:37.780 --> 18:41.540
all these years,
'cause clearly you are lovely,

18:41.575 --> 18:43.936
and he liked you.
He really did.

18:43.971 --> 18:46.535
It's just that the timing
just wasn't right,

18:46.570 --> 18:49.876
because, you see, we met
going up to the Indy 500,

18:49.911 --> 18:51.257
and, um, well...

18:52.099 --> 18:53.284
(sighs)
To tell you the truth,

18:53.616 --> 18:57.631
um, I slept with him
on the second date,

18:58.189 --> 18:59.463
which I never
really do!

18:59.760 --> 19:01.694
But you know, I was
a nice girl then--

19:01.729 --> 19:05.084
As were you, I mean, obviously,
'cause you didn't put out.

19:05.369 --> 19:09.761
And good for you. So I just
hope that all of this

19:09.796 --> 19:13.373
doesn't make you think
differently about my family,

19:13.408 --> 19:14.707
- because--
- Frankie.

19:14.742 --> 19:15.711
- (sighs)
- (toilet flushes)

19:18.138 --> 19:20.178
I got over your husband
a long time ago.

19:20.213 --> 19:21.053
(sighs)

19:21.424 --> 19:22.076
Thank God.

19:22.525 --> 19:23.931
Well, you should
count your blessings,

19:23.966 --> 19:27.162
because believe me, he really
is no picnic to live with.

19:27.227 --> 19:31.539
But he's a good dad!
Oh, such a great dad.

19:32.911 --> 19:36.253
Frankie, I'm not supposed
to tell you any information

19:36.288 --> 19:37.613
until the report is filed.

19:38.304 --> 19:40.519
- But you're fine.
- We are?

19:40.607 --> 19:45.093
Do you have any idea the kind of
crazy families I see in my job?

19:45.128 --> 19:47.819
Trust me, meeting yours was
the best part of my week--

19:48.469 --> 19:49.922
- My month.
- Really?

19:50.183 --> 19:53.148
Really. As soon as I file
my report with my supervisor,

19:53.183 --> 19:54.720
your case will
be officially closed,

19:54.754 --> 19:57.036
and then you can go on
with your life.

19:57.071 --> 19:59.403
Oh, thank you.
Oh!

19:59.787 --> 20:01.380
I'm so sorry
to have bothered you.

20:01.415 --> 20:03.769
I promise you I will
not bother you again.

20:04.518 --> 20:05.944
<i>Actually, that was a lie.</i>

20:05.979 --> 20:09.184
<i>I couldn't go home without</i>
<i>actually seeing it in writing.</i>

20:09.219 --> 20:10.943
- (computer beeps)
- (speaks indistinctly)

20:15.074 --> 20:17.020
(mouths words)

20:18.172 --> 20:20.293
<i>I don't think I ever knew</i>
<i>what relief meant</i>

20:20.328 --> 20:21.470
<i>until that moment.</i>

20:21.851 --> 20:23.808
<i>There was an upside to all</i>
<i>that happened, though.</i>

20:24.289 --> 20:26.341
<i>I had written proof</i>
<i>that I was a good parent,</i>

20:26.376 --> 20:28.509
<i>and believe me,</i>
<i>it came in handy.</i>

20:29.101 --> 20:33.553
Whoa! I cannot believe that you
won't let me go car skiing.

20:33.823 --> 20:37.298
It's safe. There's a spotter car
that follows right behind.

20:39.895 --> 20:42.234
Oh, my God.
You are the worst mom ever.

20:42.609 --> 20:46.457
Really? The state of Indiana
seems to disagree.

20:47.359 --> 20:49.899
<i>Yep. It was good to have it</i>
<i>in writing.</i>

